**user**:
> I'm trying to make a fun drink for a kid's party. I have lemonade, but I also have a smoothie maker and frozen fruit, and the kids love that. I'm wondering if I can premake the smoothie stuff, or make some kind of lemonade smoothie mix.
**assistant**:
> That sounds like a fun idea! Combining lemonade with a smoothie can make a refreshing and fruity drink that kids will love. Hereâ€™s a simple recipe for a Lemonade Smoothie Mix that you can premake and serve at the party:
> 
> ### Lemonade Smoothie Mix Recipe
> 
> #### Ingredients:
> - 2 cups of lemonade
> - 1 cup frozen strawberries
> - 1 cup frozen blueberries
> - 1 cup frozen pineapple chunks
> - 1 banana (optional, for added creaminess)
> - 1 cup of ice
> 
> #### Instructions:
> 1. **Prepare the Smoothie Base:** In your smoothie maker, blend the frozen strawberries, blueberries, pineapple chunks, and the banana until they are well combined.
> 2. **Add Lemonade:** Pour the lemonade into the blender with the mixed fruits. Blend until the mixture is smooth. The lemonade will add a nice tangy flavor to the smoothie.
> 3. **Add Ice:** Add the ice to the blender and blend again until the mixture is smooth and has a slushy consistency.
> 4. **Storage:** Pour the mixture into a sealable container and keep it in the freezer until you are ready to serve it. 
> 
> #### Serving:
> - **Before Serving:** Take the mixture out of the freezer about 10-15 minutes before serving to let it soften enough to be pourable.
> - **Cup Prep:** You could also do a fun rim on the cups with some sugar or colorful sprinkles. Lightly moisten the rims of the cups with water or a little lemonade and dip the rims into sugar or sprinkles for a festive touch.
> 
> #### Tips:
> - **Customization:** Feel free to adjust the fruit ratios based on what you have or what your kids like the most.
> - **Garnishes:** Add fun garnishes like colorful straws, umbrella picks, or fruit slices on the rim of the cup.
> 
> This Lemonade Smoothie Mix is easy to make ahead of time and will be a big hit with the kids at the party! Enjoy!
